cs.DC, cs.THEORY, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.SYSCON

Reasoning: 
1. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - The paper explicitly discusses the relationship between self-assembly phenomena and distributed computing, and presents a simulation of the wait-free consensus problem in distributed systems using tile assembly systems. 
2. cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) - The paper presents a formalization of the intuition that self-assembly phenomena are related to distributed computing, and defines a strengthened version of the consensus problem. 
3. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the simulation of consensus algorithms using tile assembly systems, which involves the design and analysis of algorithms for self-assembly. 
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the complexity of simulating the strengthened consensus problem using tile assembly systems, and compares the capabilities of two-dimensional and three-dimensional tile assembly models. 
5. cs.SYSCON (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the management of binding errors in tile assembly, which is related to the control of self-assembly processes.
